Reasoning: The paper focuses on visual recognition tasks, specifically image and video understanding, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of mid-level representation and learning of visual patterns also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of webly-supervised learning, which involves utilizing web data, and could place it under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of motion and appearance information in videos could also place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the study of dataset bias could place it under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
